{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772145653,"nonce":"P9oJbcMmvUiWHaGGxWtFBi/E8z4=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87uTmTr","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/304","origin":"github"},"title":"Allow skills to create worktrees without requiring a GitHub issue","message":"## Problem\n\nSkills that commit changes (like `/research`) currently have no way to create worktrees and PRs without a dedicated GitHub issue. The workspace's issue-first policy and `worktree_create.sh` both require `--issue \u003cN\u003e`.\n\nFor lightweight, recurring skill operations — updating a research digest, refreshing project knowledge — creating a full GitHub issue each time is unnecessary overhead. But since `main` is protected, these skills can't commit directly either.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nAdd `--skill \u003cname\u003e` as an alternative to `--issue \u003cN\u003e` across the worktree scripts:\n\n### Worktree script changes\n\n- **`worktree_create.sh`**: Accept `--skill \u003cname\u003e` as alternative to `--issue`. Generate a timestamp-based synthetic ID (e.g., `research-20260226-143022`) for branch naming (`skill/\u003cid\u003e`) and worktree path (`skill-\u003cslug\u003e-\u003cid\u003e`). Skip issue validation. Modify draft PR body to omit \"Closes #N\".\n- **`worktree_enter.sh`**: Accept `--skill \u003cname\u003e`, find skill worktrees by globbing `skill-*-\u003cname\u003e-*` directories. Set `WORKTREE_SKILL` env var.\n- **`worktree_remove.sh`**: Accept `--skill \u003cname\u003e`, matching enter script logic.\n- **`worktree_list.sh`**: Handle `skill-` prefix in display (may already work if generic enough).\n\n### Policy and documentation changes\n\n- **`AGENTS.md`**: Update issue-first policy to exempt skills that maintain living documents (research, gather-project-knowledge). Still require worktrees and PRs.\n- **`research/SKILL.md`**: Update workflow to use `--skill research` for worktree creation and push+PR instead of direct commits.\n\n### What stays the same\n\n- Issue-based worktree workflow (fully backward compatible)\n- PR requirement (still required for all changes)\n- Skills that don't commit (brainstorm, audit-*, review-*)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `worktree_create.sh --skill research --type workspace` creates a worktree\n- [ ] `worktree_enter.sh --skill research` enters the worktree\n- [ ] `worktree_remove.sh --skill research` cleans up\n- [ ] Error if neither `--issue` nor `--skill` provided\n- [ ] Error if both `--issue` and `--skill` provided\n- [ ] Issue-based workflow unchanged\n- [ ] AGENTS.md documents the skill-mode exception\n- [ ] Research skill updated to use worktree + PR workflow\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}